<p align="right"><table border=1 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0 bordercolor="#cc3333" noshade><tr><td>Deadline for submissions is <b>November 1st, 2001</b>!</td></tr></table></p>
<p>Our 2002 Conference Program will be taking place next May 21, 22, and 23 in Los Angeles at the L.A. Convention Center. We invite you join our Conference Program faculty as a workshop leader, workshop participant, panel moderator, or panelist.</p>  

<p>As a faculty member, you have the opportunity to educate and share your knowledge of what's going on in today's game industry with a core group of industry professionals who attend E<sup>3</sup> not just for the excitement of the show floor, but also for the opportunity to improve their business and creative skills.</p>

<p>Whether your expertise is in marketing, wireless gaming, packaging, the online experience, retail, software development, or graphics, your ideas for a panel discussion or workshop topic may find a home in the Conference Program at the upcoming E<sup>3</sup>.</p>

<p>If you're interested in submitting your proposal, please complete the following form. </p>

<p>We're looking for new, inventive, and exciting topics. If you have one, we invite you to communicate with us today.</p>

<p>Remember our ground rules for participating in the Conference Program: </p>
<ol>
<li>Your participation should be in the spirit of commitment to your peers in the computer game industry. 
<li>All faculty members are responsible for their own travel and lodging. E<sup>3</sup> Show Management does not offer any fees or remuneration for appearances on panels or in workshops.
<li>This is not a sales opportunity.  
<li>As an E<sup>3</sup> Conference Program faculty member, we consider you a VIP guest of E<sup>3</sup>.  Registration is complimentary and a conference faculty badge allows you to attend all conference sessions and gives you access to the show floor and keynote address.
</ul>

<p>All accepted speakers will be notified by the end of December. Your affiliation as a speaker will be used in all appropriate marketing materials.</p>

<p>Please send us your submissions by <b>November 1st</b> - and don't forget to visit the E<sup>3</sup> site often for updates to the program.</p>

<p>We appreciate your time and interest in the 2002 E<sup>3</sup> Conference Program!</p>

